<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Age-Appropriate Starting Points</h2>

<p>Not every child is ready for the full ruleset. The key is matching complexity to their reading level and attention span. Start simple, then add rules as confidence grows.</p>

<div class="overflow-x-auto my-6">
<table class="w-full text-sm">
  <thead><tr class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800"><th class="p-2 text-left">Age</th><th class="p-2 text-left">Version</th><th class="p-2 text-left">Modifications</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td class="p-2">5-6</td><td class="p-2">Scrabble Junior (two-sided board)</td><td class="p-2">Match letters to pre-printed words</td></tr>
    <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="p-2">7-8</td><td class="p-2">Regular board, simplified rules</td><td class="p-2">Open racks, 5 tiles, dictionary allowed</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="p-2">9-10</td><td class="p-2">Standard rules</td><td class="p-2">Full 7 tiles, hidden racks, time limits optional</td></tr>
    <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="p-2">11+</td><td class="p-2">Full competitive rules</td><td class="p-2">Challenges, premium squares, endgame strategy</td></tr>
